nd Leanne Betasamosake Simpson, playwrights Hannah Moscovitch and Anna Chatterton, and filmmakers Sarah Polley and Mina Shum. Writing for children as well as memoirs, autobiographies, comic books, and cookbooks illustrate the wide and impressive range of women’s talents.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Canadian.2bisacsh  aAlice Munro.  aCanada.  aCanadian culture.  aMargaret Atwood.  aMassey Commission.  aTRC.  adiversity.  adrama.  afiction.  afilm.  aliterary criticism.  aliterary studies.  aliterature.  amusic.  anon-fiction.  awomen’s writing.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishz978311061036908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2019z9783110606348oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065206240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753424040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487534240423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487534240.jpg  a978-3-11-061036-9  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-065206-2  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DKUb2019